text: Abdullahi El Kory (born 31 December 1990) is a Mauritanian footballer who plays as midfielder for Emirates Club . ==Career== Abdullahi El Kory had played for several Mauritanian clubs such as Zamzam, Nasr Tiaret and the Dean of Mauritanian Clubs Association ACS Ksar and won with him the Mauritanian Cup, before moving to the Emirates where he played in the League of Institutions with several clubs and won several other football championships before he announced his joining the Emirates Club , That would be the second Mauritanian footballer to take part in the Emirates league, after former Egyptian Al Ahly SC striker Dominique Da Sylva, who was a professional player with Al Urooba. ولد الكوري يحترف في الدوري الإماراتي ==Honours== ACS Ksar *Coupe du Président de la République: 1 :: 2014 ==References== == External links == * Category:1990 births Category:Living people Category:Mauritanian footballers Category:Mauritanian expatriate footballers Category:Association football midfielders Category:Emirates Club players Category:UAE Pro League players Category:UAE First Division League players Category:Expatriate footballers in the United Arab Emirates Category:Mauritanian expatriate sportspeople in the United Arab Emirates
